({The exchange of bishops with} 13... Bd3 14. Ng3 Bxf1 15. Rxf1 {made Black's
structural drawback (especially the weak f5-spot) even more significant in
Plazuelo Pascual,J - Andres Gonzalez,I Linares 2019}) 14. Ng3 a4 15. a3 Bf8 {
This was Perez Ponsa,F - Grischuk,A Krasnaya Polyana 2021 White could have
exploited the drawback of Black's artificial play with} 16. f4 $1 $146 Be4 {
The only way to liberate the poor bishop on g6} 17. Nxe4 dxe4 18. Rc1 h5 19. g3
$14 {Black has no compensation for his weak kingside pawns.}) 13. g3 {White
also accepts possible damage to his pawn structure. However, it will cost
Black his strong dark-squared bishop.} Bxh4 ({In case of} 13... Nf8 14. Ng2 Ne6
{Tomaszewski,K - Grabarczyk,M Szklarska Poreba 2017 White should lock the
bishop with} 15. Nef4 Bb4+ 16. Ke2 $14 {, and then it will be a long torture
for Black.}) 14. gxh4 {White gets the g-file and the f4-outpost for his knight.
} Nf6 {A clever idea - the strong f4-knight should be neutralized as soon as
possible.} ({Too passive is} 14... Ke7 15. Nf4 h6 16. b4 $1 {White seizes more
space on the other side, too.} Nf8 17. Rg1 Kf6 18. h5 Bh7 19. Nd3 Ne6 20. f4
$16 {Black was positionally busted. Moiseenko,A - Cyborowski,L Germany 2016})
15. Rg1 {This logical move has only been seen in a few games so far. White
involves the rook, so potentially the f5-pawn might become weaker.} ({Less
energetic is} 15. Bg2 Ke7 16. Ng3 f4 17. exf4 Nh5 $11 {Navara,D - Bacrot, E
Linares 2020}) ({Tournament practice proves that converting the minimal edge
after} 15. Nf4 Nh5 16. Kd2 Nxf4 17. exf4 {is a tough task because of the
simplistic nature of the position.}) 15... Ke7 ({In the event of} 15... Nh5 {
