14. Qd2 $1 cxd4 {14...Rg8 is possible, but this is too ugly. White will push
d4-d5 and obtain the better position.} 15. Rxg7 $1 Kxg7 16. Qxh6+ Kg8 17. Rb5
$1 {The rook is joining the attack on time.} f6 18. Qg6+ Kh8 19. Rf5 {Black is
on the verge of collapse.}) 14. Bb5 $1 {Preparation for the key break.} Bb7 15.
d5 exd5 16. exd5 Na5 17. Ne5 $36 {Black's king got under strong pressure in
Giri, A - Wei,Y Chess.com INT 2020}) 11. cxd4 {The strong pawn centre and the
advanced h-pawn are a cause of worry, even though Black currently has some
development advantages.} Bb4+ ({Black cannot afford to ignore White's
